    This is hands down the best take out food in the area - we are so happy to have found it.  The food is authentic and delicious on all accounts and we keep coming back for more.  The people that work there could not be nicer and are so helpful with any requests you might have.  My husband went to pick up our latest take out order yesterday and when he mentioned it was for my birthday, they went over the top with our food.  Absolutely made me feel special (and full) on an otherwise lacking birthday!  Their falafel is the best I've ever had in San Diego and their hummus is PROPER hummus, unlike the stuff you get in a plastic container at the store.  We will be back many more times - that is for sure!

    We've been here several times and the food has been consistent and delicious. They are now open for dine in which is a great option for lunch. Our favorites are the chicken and garlic wrap, honest chicken bowl, and chicken shish tawook plate. Their sauces are mouth watering. The food is an explosion of flavors in your mouth and fresh.

One of our orders was heavy on the salt and we informed him about the issue. Not only did he remake the food without question and apologized, he also gave us complimentary baklava and personally came to check on our food after it got remade to make sure we were satisfied. I just wanted to highlight the excellent work from Isaac and his outstanding service to his customers. He has our business for the years to come!

    It's a better option for dining in than carryout.

    Walking into simsim is like walking into chipotle without the the option of picking your ingredients. Their menu is hard to read but we were able to select a few things that sounded good. They did warn us that it would take 15 minutes to make..

    As we were waiting in the dining room we could see the amazing plates that people were eating. The dishes looked and smelled delicious.

    The BEST thing about simsim was their self serve sauce bar which included unlimited garlic sauce!! We grabbed a ton of containers. The food was fine, perhaps they were a bit frugal on the fries.

    In summation, Simsim's to-go service didn't quite capture the dine in experience. I recently tried the fast-casual restaurant Tahini and their to go food style was better.

    - These guys also bailed out on a Yelp Eite Week event... We will never forget..

    Comment from Nawar M. of Simsim Outstanding Shawarma

    Business Owner

    6/8/2020Marcus,

    Thank you for visiting Simsim and taking the time to leave a review - we value all feedback be it positive or constructive. We are sorry about the to go orders not meeting expectations, we have been actively looking at ways to make sure our product tastes the same at home as in the store even with travel between places. Additionally we are in the middle of redesigning our menu to in fact make it easier to read.

    Due to COVID-19 we removed the self service station to meet health requirements and ensure guest safety.

    As it relates to the Yelp Elite Event, we in fact did want to host a 1-2 week event however we wanted Yelpers to dine with us and pay full price - however, we were willing to donate 100% of our profit during the event period (regardless of yelp elite person or not) to a mutually agreed charity. Unfortunately, Yelp was not open to that idea at the time.

    I do hope you give us another chance in the future, we are in the middle of some concept changes that we hope to launch by the end of July/Early August.

    Stay safe and healthy.  

    Best regards,

    Nawar Miri
    President

    I must say this was by far one of the hottest, most delicious Mediterranean spots in San Diego. The place is very clean and well managed.

    We came in and sat down in the front tables. One of the servers came over and greeted us with some desserts. Now that's some top notch customer service in a place where everyone needs to place their orders at the counter.

    Variety of selections from kebabs to platters to shawarmas and vegetarian  options. Feel free to ask questions since they would most likely know what you would like

    We ordered bunch of stuff and I can't emphasize enough on how amazing and delicious each dish was. Tender juicy chicken kebabs, fresh organic tenderloin steak and tasty lamb beef kebab. You just can't go wrong with any of these.

    We live very close by so I'm sure this will become our usual spot soon

    Keep up the amazing work guys!!
